4 A BILL
5 TO BE ENTITLED
6 AN ACT
7
8
9 Relating to Escambia County; to authorize the sheriff,
10 county commission, and a municipality to contract for the
11 sheriff to provide police services for the municipality; to
12 provide for the expenditure of funds; and to authorize the
13 county commission to provide a supplemental salary to the
14 sheriff for the performance of additional duties relating to
15 the contracting of police services for a municipality.
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
17 Section 1. (a) Any municipality within Escambia County
18 may contract with the Sheriff of Escambia County for police
19 services. The contract may include enforcement by the sheriff,
20 or his or her duly commissioned deputies, of all laws within
21 the corporate limits and police jurisdiction of the
22 municipality, including municipal ordinances, and the arrest
23 or citation of any offenders as if the sheriff, or his or her
24 duly commissioned deputies, were duly constituted police
25 officers of the municipality.
26 (b) A municipality entering into a contract pursuant to
27 subsection (a) shall pay to the county treasury a sum
28 sufficient to provide the necessary manpower and equipment as
Page 1

sufficient to provide the necessary manpower and equipment as
HB441 INTRODUCED
29 mutually agreed upon by the municipal governing body, the
30 sheriff, and the county commission.
31 (c) The county commission shall receive from the
32 municipality the funds paid under the contract for police
33 services and may expend funds for police services in the
34 municipality, including the police jurisdiction of the
35 municipality.
36 (d) Each contract between the sheriff and a
37 municipality must have the consent and approval of the sheriff
38 and the county commission.
39 (e) The sheriff and his or her duly commissioned
40 deputies, in the performance of any duties carried out
41 pursuant to a contract with a municipality, shall retain the
42 legal and constitutional immunity afforded to each of them by
43 law.
44 (f)(1) The Escambia County Commission may by resolution
45 of the commission provide a supplemental salary to the sheriff
46 for the performance of additional duties relating to the
47 contracting of police services for a municipality. The
48 performance of additional duties relating to the contracting
49 of police services for a municipality by the sheriff shall be
50 pursuant to an agreement between the sheriff and the county
51 commission subject to approval of the county commission.
52 (2) The supplemental salary shall be paid by the county
53 for the performance of additional duties by the sheriff and
54 shall not be considered a part of the regular salary of the
55 sheriff. In the event the county commission or sheriff
56 withdraws from the agreement, the supplemental salary shall be
Page 2

withdraws from the agreement, the supplemental salary shall be
HB441 INTRODUCED
57 discontinued. The supplemental salary provided by this
58 subsection shall not affect or increase the compensation of
59 any supernumerary sheriff in the county.
60 Section 2. This act shall become effective on June 1,
61 2026.
